title: Lead Analytics Engineer

With over 20 years in the field, he has held various roles, from DBA to Investment Relations and M&A analyst, before returning to data warehousing to lead successful projects at Just Eat and Virgin Media O2. At Just Eat, Gordon played a key role in reducing costs and streamlining operations by developing data models, denormalizing data, and implementing Airflow across Analytics and Data Science teams. He reduced onboarding times for new analysts and made it easy for the team to enrich their data knowledge while reducing costs.  With his hard work and dedication in 2020 he won the employee of the year award and his team the Data Modelling Team (Later Analytics Engineering) won team of the year.  2023 he was part of the VMO2 Data Platform Team that won Google's DORA for 'Optimizing for Speed without sacrificing Stability'. At Virgin Media O2, Gordon has led the data warehouse development and migration from on-premise to GCP Big Query, redesigned the data infrastructure, and introduced DBT to over 170 users across Analytics, MLOPS, and Data Science, resulting in improved efficiency, cost savings and opening the door to new innovation. Gordon is a natural leader and mentor, known for his ability to build high-performing teams. He is passionate about innovation and continually seeks out new ways to leverage data and technology to drive business value. His go-to books are Project Unicorn and The Toyota Way, which he considers essential reading/studying for his teams as he and the team continue to focuses on efficiency, quality, and continuous improvement.

bio:
Mark Matteucci is a seasoned professional with a dynamic career encompassing analytics engineering, finance, and operations. Mark obtained his MBA in 2009 and since then, has taken on influential roles at tech giants including Cisco, Workday, Medallia, and Zoom. In each of these roles, Mark has demonstrated an innate ability to bridge the gap between technology and business. He has used this ability to effectively combine analytics with financial and operational expertise, providing valuable insights that enhance efficiency, fuel revenue growth, and bolster strategic initiatives.
Currently at dbt Labs, Inc., Mark is pioneering the use of data warehousing and data pipelines to automate operational workflows in General & Administrative (G&A) functions. His innovative approach has revolutionized the role of analytics within G&A, streamlining operations and allowing for more data-driven decision-making processes.
Mark is thrilled to share his experiences and insights at Coalesce. As a speaker, he will be engaging with fellow analytics engineers on the importance of integrating analytics into strategic planning and execution, the evolving role of analytics in modern business, and the potential of using data to automate G&A workflows.

In his current role, Oliver has spearheaded the development of the core data models on the Google Cloud Platform (GCP) using dbt. His visionary leadership and technical prowess have led to the creation of a robust infrastructure that empowers data-driven decision-making across the organization.

Prior to his role at Virgin Media O2, Oliver's impact was felt at Just Eat, where his work played a pivotal role in understanding and reporting the operational implications of the global Covid pandemic on the business. His insights not only guided strategic decisions but also enabled the organization to navigate unprecedented challenges effectively. Additionally, this model was instrumental in securing the partnership of the largest restaurant chain, showcasing his ability to translate complex data into actionable strategies.

Oliver's journey in the realm of data commenced at Paddy Power Betfair, where he initiated the development of a robust process to detect and counteract unauthorized market data scraping by external entities. His innovative thinking and analytical acumen were key in safeguarding critical business information, demonstrating his commitment to data integrity and security.

title: Analytics Engineer
bio:
Starting his career in mechanical engineering with an emphasis on large machinery, Chris’s interests and skills led him towards medical robotics. His professional evolution took him to Intuitive, where he played a key role in the manufacturing of the da Vinci surgical robot.

Driven by his innovative spirit, Chris transitioned to a failure analysis and design engineer role for the daVinci surgical Stapler. With the goal to help with failure analysis, he assembled a basic “data platform” for the stapler team. This system, mainly composed of stored procedures and SQL queries, offered a means for rapid analysis of procedures, customer experiences, and field performance of the stapler.

This side project was a precursor of his future trajectory. Chris was able to join a team of like minded data folks who together have evolved the initial data platform into a sophisticated infrastructure, with dbt at its core!

title: Software Engineer
bio:
I am originally from Bordeaux, France :wine_glass:

Before joining Intuitive Surgical, I used to work in academia as a research mathematician, specializing in differential geometry. I had a lot of fun and lived in a bunch of different countries: France, Brazil, the US, Germany, and the US again.

My transition to the tech industry started during the pandemic, as my research interests shifted to computational geometry and its application to data science and machine learning. In April 2022, I joined Intuitive’s data platform team. I also settled in New York City with my partner Benjamin, who is a musical theater composer/lyricist.

My main occupation at Intuitive has been the development and expansion of our dbt ecosystem. I am for sure a dbt enthusiast :dbt-party:

Her excitement comes from using data science to break through the surface layer of information to help formulate actionable business insights. She has advised and worked with companies such as Southwest Airlines, McAfee, Universal Pictures, and City of Hope, to name a few.

title: Head of Data
bio: Sean Rober is the Head of Data at Avenue One, leading the efforts for data & analytics engineering. He has previously run the data team at Zenefits and held roles in finance, product & strategy at Sunrun and JPMorgan.

title: Senior Staff Engineer
bio: Chris is currently a Senior Staff Engineer at Udemy where he works on the Data & Analytics Platform team. He graduated from Cornell University in 2015 with a degree in Applied Economics and has been working in the data industry in various capacities from Data Scientist to Data Engineer, from mid-sized startups to large enterprise companies. In his free time, Chris enjoys watching movies and following anti-authoritarian social movements.

title: Senior Field Engineering Manager
bio: Thor List is a Senior Field Engineering Manager at Databricks and over the last almost 5 years he has built up a team of 40 talented Solutions Architects to help Enterprise customers in Northern Europe solve their most challenging data and AI problems. Before joining Databricks he spent a lot of time building collaborative robots, computer and face recognition systems and covert surveillance equipment for governments around the world.

title: Sr. Data Engineer
bio: Elize Papineau's career started in biotech building lab-prep automation applications and analytics pipelines to enable research teams. She has since spent time in both customer-facing and internal analytics engineering roles, crafting delectable datasets across industries and tech stacks. Currently, Elize is defining the platform function at dbt Labs - supporting the internal data team in Snowflake administration, dbt Cloud job orchestration, and custom data ingestion. Some would say she drinks too much iced tea 😉🧋

title: Analytics Lead
bio: Brandon has been in the analytics space since undergrad, where he received his degree in Business Competitive Intelligence. From there, he moved on to the world of PR & marketing analytics helping some of the world’s largest brands measure the impact of their efforts. When he’s not thinking about campaign optimization and attribution modeling, Brandon spends his time recreating in the mountains near where he lives in Salt Lake City.

title: Head of Product Marketing
bio: Eric leads Product Marketing at RudderStack, a high-growth startup in the data space. He leads management of their internal data stack, including the data pipelines that drive marketing reporting and activation. He has over a decade of experience working with and implementing customer data infrastructure and has advised companies like BMW, WeWork and a host of startups on marketing strategy and data related projects.

title: CEO & Co-Founder
bio: Boris is the co-founder and CEO of Census, the leading Data Activation platform that helps companies like Canva, Sonos, and Notion revolutionize data-driven marketing. Previously, he was the co-founder and CEO of Meldium, a modern identity management platform for SaaS, acquired by LogMeIn in 2014. He is an advisor and alumnus of Y Combinator. Prior to that, Boris was a Senior Product Manager at Microsoft, working on developer tools like Visual Studio Code. He enjoys nerding out about data and technology, helping other startup founders, and angel investing.

title: Director of Data & Analytics
bio: Jeff Chen is the Director of Data & Analytics at Fleetio. Prior to Fleetio, he led data teams at a variety of companies, from B2C startups to private, enterprise-size data vendors. Jeff has been working in the data space for the last 10 years as both an individual contributor and manager. His data background is really as a Data Engineer, starting in the early AWS days with Hadoop, Spark, and then cloud data warehouses. He discovered dbt in early 2020 and immediately embraced the modern data stack as the better alternative, never looking back. Aside from data engineering, Jeff has experience with leading data ops, data science, and analytics and reporting. He finds incredible joy and satisfaction in helping companies solve their process or business problems with data and helping people discover insights that they didn't have before. Jeff is a geek at heart and loves playing with all the cool technologies and tools in the data space. Additionally, he's had the privilege of working in a multitude of different industries, from telecom to B2C, and loves how varied the data that each industry and company has because there's always something new and different to learn about.

title: Director, Data & Analytics
bio: Jason is an accomplished consultant with over a decade of experience working with Fortune 50 companies. With a passion for driving business success through data-driven insights, Jason has established a track record of delivering impactful results for clients across a range of industries. In the past three years, Jason has taken on a new challenge as the driving force behind a start-up's analytics program. Leveraging his expertise and insights, he has played a crucial role in shaping the company's direction and driving growth through analytics. Jason holds an undergraduate degree from Ball State University, as well as graduate degrees from the University of Cincinnati and Columbia University in the City of New York. Outside of work, Jason is a devoted husband and father to one daughter, and makes his home in beautiful Portland, OR.

title: CEO
bio: Gleb Mezhanskiy is the CEO & Co-founder of Datafold, an automated data testing solution for data & analytics engineers. Before starting Datafold, Gleb was a founding data team member at multiple companies including Autodesk & Lyft

title: Head/Director of Data
bio: Santona Tuli, PhD began her data journey through fundamental physics—searching through massive event data from particle collisions at CERN to detect rare particles. She’s since extended her machine learning engineering to natural language processing, before switching focus to product and data engineering for data workflow authoring frameworks. At Astronomer, she helped improve the development experience for data science and machine learning pipelines in popular data orchestration tool, Airflow. Currently at Upsolver, she leads data engineering and science, driving developer research and product strategy for declarative workflow authoring in SQL. Dr. Tuli is passionate about building, as well as empowering others to build, end-to-end data and ML pipelines, scalably.

title: Senior Data Scientist
bio: David is a data engineer from dv01, a Fitch Solutions company. As the tech lead for a dbt pipeline, David has helped dv01 achieve scalability on an analytics suite for clients in the loan warehousing space. He also manages machine learning models that power portfolio analysis of asset backed securities. Outside of work David is an avid tennis player and passionate about Brazilian dances.

title: Sr. Director of Data Science and Analytics
bio: Bill Lynch has spend the last 10+ years at start-ups and scale-ups, last 5+ in mental health tech at NeuroFlow, a Philadelphia based behavioral health tech company looking to improve the efficiency and scalability of our client's programs so that we can ultimately help them improve illness, well-being, and overall health while also lowering the cost of care. I am a founding team employee and have built the data team from the ground up while also creating our risk stratification and suicidal ideation detection data products. As such, I am passionate about building high functioning data teams, strong data cultures, and making an impact on today's mental health crisis.

title: Director of Partner Engineering, Sigma Computing
bio: Nate Meinzer has over 10 years experience as a data platform architect and is passionate about creating human-centric data products that engage users, uncover insights, and empower organizations to derive the most value from their data.

title: Analytics Engineer
bio: Amanda Fioritto is an analytics engineer at Hex. She previously held data roles at Spin and Sonder; and in a previous life, she was a data-loving policy wonk working to improve American public education one spreadsheet at a time. When she's not at her desk, you can find her curled up with a good book, hiking with her fiancé and pup, or making a mess in the kitchen.

title: Lead Developer Advocate

bio: Former Data Engineer turned TPM @ FanDuel NYC

title: Senior Data Engineer
bio: Mike Lee was one of the first employees to start using dbt at Fanduel. He's seen the transformative impact it can have on a company and understands the long-term process it requires to implement. He now works on the Data Architecture team at Fanduel, helping scale warehousing solutions to meet new dbt needs.

title: Manager, Data Science Analytics
bio: Will has worked in the data space within manufacturing for over 10 years. From Tesla to now Rivian, he's worked on structuring, serving, and analyzing high variety datasets from people and machines to help new factories ramp up.

title: Vice President, Brand Marketing
bio: As Vice President of Brand Marketing, Alyssa Smrekar leads dbt Labs' Strategic Events, Community, Comms, Content and Social Media programs. She has extensive B2B marketing leadership experience, having served in similar roles at Okta and Intercom.

title: Analytics Engineering Manager
bio: Sandra Herchen is an Analytics Engineering Manager with 5 years of experience working in data. She was the first analytics engineer on her team at Snowflake, and has since built out the entire engineering group supporting Finance. When she's not working, you can find Sandra at the park with her two dogs, or playing basketball & golf.

title: Product Manager
bio: Roxi is a Product Manager at dbt Labs working on the Semantic Layer. She joined with Transform acquisition and has been working on the Semantic Layer for the last two and a half years.

title: Director of Data Engineering
bio: Ravi is the Director of Data Engineering at Moody’s Analytics – Commercial Real Estate division. In his current role, Ravi manages central Data Warehouse and Machine learning operations. Throughout his career, Ravi has led high performing teams to build Data and Machine Learning pipelines.  Ravi has an M.S from Birla Institute of Technology and Science (BITS) and an MBA from Lehigh University. Ravi lives in Chester Springs, PA with his wife and kids and enjoys Orienteering on weekends.

title: Senior Data Engineer
bio: Alex Rong is a Senior Data Engineer at Domain, a leading Australian property marketplace. He is also a dbt open source contributor and was previously a data engineer at Brighte and Foxtel. Alex graduated from Shanghai University with a B.S. in Materials Sciences and from the University of New South Wales with a master's in Information Technology.

title: Data Engineer
bio: Ryan is a Data Engineer at Moody's Analytics. In his current role, Ryan leads dbt initiatives and the machine learning operations team within the Commercial Real Estate (CRE) division. Previously, Ryan worked in the Economics division where he developed credit risk data pipelines. Ryan has a degree from Drexel University and now resides in West Chester, PA with his fiancé and their dog, Bailey. In his free time, he enjoys building wooden furniture to display in his home.

title: Data Engineer
bio: Reuben Francis is a data engineer at Domain, a leading Australian property marketplace. Reuben specializes in data analysis, transformation, and orchestration. He graduated from the Institute of Aeronautical Engineering with a bachelor's in Computer Science and from Macquarie University with a master's in Data Science.

title: Data Platform Engineer
bio: Christy Cao is a skilled data platform engineer with a passion for designing and implementing robust data pipelines and infrastructure to support efficient data processing and analytics. With over 3 years of experience in the field, Christy has a deep understanding of data integration, data modeling and data warehousing. As a Data Platform Engineer at Salesforce, Christy is responsible for designing and developing scalable ELT processes and ensuring data quality and integration, she has successfully implemented various data engineering solutions, leveraging cutting-edge technologies such as AWS, Matillion and dbt. Christy holds a Bachelor degree in Management Information System and a Master degree in Business Analytics. She is passionate about leveraging her technical expertise to drive data innovation and enable data-driven decision making within organizations.

title: VP - Director of Product Ownership | Data Strategy
bio: Kayleigh Lavorini serves as a vice president and Director of Agile Product Ownership & Data Strategy at Fifth Third Bank. In this role, she is responsible for bringing the Fifth Third Data Mesh to life – with a focus on building foundational data architecture patterns and services that will allow Fifth Third achieve decentralized data ownership at scale. Kayleigh has been in IT at Fifth Third for 3 years with several roles focused on data and self-service technology, partnering with various lines of business to build comprehensive analytics solutions.

title: Data Analyst
bio: Faith has had a patchwork career starting in animal behavior research, then moving into education, and now she has settled down in the data world. She currently works in data driven risk management for perishable goods, and gets to be involved with cool projects like assessing risk and performance of vaccines being distributed across the supply chain of Senegal. Outside of work, Faith loves athletic challenges like distance running and boxing. One of her proudest accomplishments is raising $10,000 for the American Cancer Society by training for a USA Boxing match. She is pleased to report getting punched in the face really isn't so bad. Faith lives in Colorado with her fiancé and their black cat, Gus. They like to spend Sunday nights watching The Last of Us and Attack on Titan. She plays a rogue with a level in warlock in Dungeons and Dragons.

title: SVP  | Senior Director, Data Engineering
bio: Ben Rottinghaus, SVP, Sr. Director, Data Management & Engineering

title: Solution Architect
bio: Dakota Kelley was born in Bartlesville, Oklahoma. Throughout most of his childhood, his family moved all over the South Central United States, but always seemed to make it back to Bartlesville. He currently lives in Edmond, Oklahoma with his lovely wife and their two dogs. From a young age, Dakota had a love for taking things apart, figuring out how they worked, and putting them back together (often frustrating his mother as she’d come home from work to find things taken apart). While he had a love of solving problems, which expressed itself as an affinity for math, he often found school itself boring. That all changed once Dakota got to high school and found he could spend half of his day in a vocational trade school known as Tri-County Technology Center. Dakota eventually enrolled in a Computer Repair and Network Engineering course and fell in love with solving problems using computers. After high school, he set off to Oklahoma State University, Institute of Technology (OSU IT) where he earned a Bachelors of Technology with a focus on Software Development, Information Assurance, and Computer Forensics. After graduating from OSU IT, Dakota took on a position as a Software Developer and spent several years working with data. Along the way, he realized he wanted to dive in and learn more. He would work during the day and spend his nights taking classes at Oklahoma State University while he pursued a MS degree, which he obtained with a 3.9 GPA in December of 2021.

title: Data Engineer
bio: Jenna has been a data engineer for the City of Boston's Analytics team since January 2022. She is proud to say that she learned how to code at library school, and graduated with a Masters of Library & Information Science from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign in May 2020. She enjoys using python and SQL to be an information magician, and still maintains that 3rd Normal Form is the best way to organize data at the foundation.

title: Solutions Architect
bio: Pat Ross is a data science, engineering, and analytics consultant who’s worked with industry giants in sectors including professional and collegiate sports, technology, retail, healthcare, finance, and non-profit organizations. Serving as Solutions Architect at Data Clymer, a next-gen consulting firm specializing in full-stack engineering and data culture transformation, he assists clients with challenges from building a modern data stack to advanced analytics and machine learning. Pat emphasizes the importance of aligning solutions with business goals and future aspirations. Outside of work, he resides in South Lake Tahoe with his girlfriend and their two dogs, enjoying activities like snowboarding, skiing, golfing, biking, and hiking throughout the year.

title: Senior Data Engineer
company: California Office of Data and Innovation
bio: Ian is a data engineer with the State of California. He's hopped around start-ups, open source, the public sector, and academia, fulfilling software engineering, data science, and data engineering roles. In a past life, he was a geologist, and will still talk your ear off about rocks given the opportunity.
